  "number": 409,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/409",
  "title": "Allow choosing on and off values to the toggle",
  "body": "Following #408 we had an idea with @Jerskouille to allow the toggle to be really usable in various toggling situations.\n\nWe can add \"on value\" and \"off value\" feature to the current toggle API.\n\nHandle \"free_shipping\" being either `true` or nothing (nothing = free + non free shipping)\n\n``` js\ntoggle({\n  facetName: 'free_shipping',\n  values: {\n    on: true\n  }\n})\n```\n\nHandle \"archived\" being either `true` or `false`:\n\n``` js\ntoggle({\n  facetName: 'archived',\n  values: {\n    on: true\n    off: false\n  }\n})\n```\n\nHandle \"fruit\" being `banana` or `oranges`:\n\n``` js\ntoggle({\n  facetName: 'fruit',\n  values: {\n    on: 'banana',\n    off: 'orange'\n  }\n})\n```\n\nHandle \"only my favorites\" or \"everything\":\n\n``` js\ntoggle({\n  facetName: '_tags',\n  values: {\n    on: 'user42'\n  }\n})\n```\n\nBe careful about the default count we send, it's right now not accurate (showing \"false\" values instead of true)\n",
  "created_at": "2015-11-02T15:56:23Z",
